annotation.documentation:
Annotations for XML Schema to indicate the API life-cycle of the various components of the schema definition. Following components should be annotated:
* element * attribute * global complex types * global simple types * attribute groups * element groups * enumeration
The annotation could be made as an attribute of the according component or as part of the annotation/appinfo element of the according component.
Example:
<element name="foo" ver:defsince="3"/>
<element name="bar" ver:defsince="3"> <complexType> <sequence> <element ref="tns:foo" ver:since="3"/> </sequence> </complexType> </element>
Indicates since which API version a component is defined within the schema. Only global type definitions (simpleType, complexType), global elements and global attributes shall be annotated.
Indicates since which API version a element or attribute is used within the schema. Global attributes and elements have to be annotated with "defsince".

The Supplier?s reference for the offer that adjusts the costs. This attribute is repeated for each day of the stay where the cost has been adjusted. A stay may cover multiple different adjusment offers. Multiple dates may have the same adjustment offer, and some dates may have no adjustment.
It may be possible for the name to be null when there is a cost adjustment. In this case the attribute will still be included in the XML - with the two attributes populated. There is no translation available for the Supplier Offer Name.
